      crossorigin="anonymous"
    />
    <style>
      body {
        background-color: #f3edc8;
        /* header colour : #7D0A0A
        body colour: #BF3131
        footer colour : #EAD196 */
        color: #f3edc8;
        font-size: 1.25rem;
      }
      #joke-body {
        background-color: #bf3131;
        height: 100%;
        color: #f3edc8;
      }
      #joke-header {
        background-color: #7d0a0a;
      }
      #joke-form {
        height: 60px;
        width: 50%;
        margin-left: 25%;
        padding: 1px;
        border: 2.5px solid whitesmoke;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        align-items: center;
        border-style: dashed;
      }
      #joke-content {
        height: 200px;
        margin-top: 10px;
        width: 50%;
        margin-left: 25%;
        padding: 10px;
        border: 6px solid whitesmoke;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        align-items: center;
        border-style: dashed;
      }
      .nav-pills .nav-link {
        color: #ead196; /* Change text color to blue */
      }
      .nav-pills .nav-link.active,
      .nav-pills .show > .nav-link {
        background-color: #bf3131; /* Change active background color to yellow */
      }
      #joke-footer {
        background-color: #ead196;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="d-flex justify-content-center py-3" id="joke-header">
      <ul class="nav nav-pills">
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a href="/" class="nav-link" aria-current="page">Home</a>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a href="/about" class="nav-link active">About</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </header>
    <div class="p-5 text-center" id="joke-body">
        <h1 class="">Tell Me A Joke</h1>
        <p class="col-lg-8 mx-auto fs-5 ">
          This is a website that tells the user a joke using the word they have provided. It's a simple little thing, made possible using <a href="https://sv443.net/jokeapi/v2/" style="color: #ead196;">JokeAPI</a>.
          <br/>JokeAPI is a free-to-use public API that provides a wide variety of jokes catering to all tastes, dark or light, explicit or safe. Sometimes, the joke may not be using your given word exactly, as it will give you any joke that uses that string of letters in any way. For instance, if you put tree, then it might give a joke using streets since it contains the word "tree".
          <br/> You can have a try on it <a href="https://sv443.net/jokeapi/v2/#try-it" style="color: #ead196;">here</a>, although its available using the above link as well.
          <br/><br/>I do not claim ownership over the API at all, in any circumstances, and give credit to the original owner of this JokeAPI, <a href="https://github.com/Sv443" style="color: #ead196;">Sven Fehler</a>.  
        </p>
        <img src="quick-fox-03.jpg" height="150px" width="150px" style="border-radius: 50%; filter: drop-shadow(0 0 10px #ead196);"/>
        <p>Created with ♥ by <a href="https://github.com/quick-fox-03" style="color:#ead196">quick-fox-03</a></p>

      </div>
